,0,NULL,1476929284,1476928984,0,0,1476673073,3,1457403529,5,'',1,0,NULL,NULL,10),(319,47,'push','内容页Guess you like','[]','[{\"contentid\":100856,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA\'S CENTRAL BANK: YUAN STABILIZING\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0318\\/100856.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0318\\/1458284337877.jpg\",\"description\":\"The People\'s Bank of China announced on Monday that its yuan funds outstanding for foreign exchange dropped 228 billion yuan, about 30 billion U.S. dollars to 24 trillion yuan in February.\\n   \\nThe fall sharply narrowed from the 644 billion decline in January and a record plunge of 708 billion yuan in December.\\n\\nThrough 2015, the funds only rose in January and October.\\n\\nAs yuan is not freely convertible under the capital account, the central bank has to purchase foreign currency generated by China\'s trade surplus and foreign investment in the country, adding funds to the money market.\\n\\nTherefore, such funds are an important indicator for foreign capital flow in and out of China as well as domestic yuan liquidity.\\n\\nAs the February data showed, China\'s foreign exchange market has in general calmed down after months of volatility.\\n\\nThe capital outflow had largely peaked in January, and the market is back to normal.\\n\\nSome experts said that the strong expectations for yuan depreciation in past months were an overreaction.\\n\\nAnd if the overall economy continues to stabilize or shows momentum for stabilization and improvement, China\'s foreign exchange market would do well.\\n\\nLast week central bank governor Zhou Xiaochuan said that the yuan had started to return to a normal and reasonable level after volatility.\\n\\nAccording to the China Foreign Exchange Trading System, the central parity rate of the renminbi weakened 166 basis points to 6.5079 against the U.S. dollar on Tuesday.\",\"time\":1458284381},{\"contentid\":100859,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA\'S POWER USE EXPANDS AS ECONOMY STABILIZES\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0318\\/100859.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0318\\/1458284447648.jpg\",\"description\":\"China\'s power consumption, a key barometer of economic activity, rose 4 percent year on year in February, reaching 381 billion kilowatt hours.\\n\\nThe National Energy Administration on Wednesday said the pace of growth accelerated from the comparable decline of 6.3 percent for the same month last year.\\n\\nIn the first two months of the year, power consumptionstood at 876 billion kwh, up two percent from one year earlier.\\n\\nOther macro indicators for the January-February period, including improved fixed-asset investment, house sales and consumption, also signal improvement in the economy.\",\"time\":1458284487},{\"contentid\":100862,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINESE CARS SHINE AT CAIRO MOTOR SHOW\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0318\\/100862.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0318\\/1458284515390.jpg\",\"description\":\"The 2016 Cairo international motor show kicks off in Egypt with a notable participation of China\'s largest vehicle manufacturers.\\n\\nThis year, the event witnessed large attendance, including car lovers and local businessmen and companies. On the opening day, Chinese corporations of Brilliance, BAIC, Chang\'an, Chery and Jac have brought their recent range of models to the six-day show. \\n\\nBrilliance Bavarian Auto presented three new cars to the Egyptian market. Brilliance has plans to invest 120 million U.S. dollars in Egypt, of which 30 million dollars has already been invested.\\n       \\nChina\'s another leading auto maker, Chery International, announced re-launching of its Speranza cars under the new name of \\\"Chery.\\\" Chery has sold over 30,000 Speranza models in Egypt since 2004 and has become the most popular Chinese car in Egypt.\\n\\nChinese cars invaded the Egyptian auto market more than a decade ago and they have proved great reliability for their high quality as well as reasonable prices.\",\"time\":1458284563},{\"contentid\":101183,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"RUSSIA KEEPS MODERATELY TIGHT MONETARY POLICY\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0321\\/101183.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0321\\/1458545913842.jpg\",\"description\":\"\\nRussia\'s central bank said the country will keep applying a moderately tight monetary policy for a longer period of time.\\n\\nAccording to the central bank, to enable the accomplishment of inflation targets, the bank may conduct its moderately tight monetary policy for a more prolonged time than previously planned.\\n\\nThe bank estimated the annual consumer price growth rate in Russia declined to 7.9 percent by March 14 from 9.8 percent in January, lower than last year\'s expectation of 9-percent inflation.\\n\\nThe bank predicted that quarterly inflation will continue declining in the second quarter of this year, while annual inflation might accelerate temporarily in the middle of the year as a result of the low base effect.\\n\\nThe bank expected Russia\'s economic downturn to slow down to 1.3-1.5 percent this year, compared with 3.7 percent last year.\\n\\nIt also forecasted a quarterly GDP rise between late 2016 and early 2017.\\n\\nAccording to the bank, further import substitution and non-energy export expansion will help a gradual economic recovery.\\n\\nThe bank added the economy will continue adjusting to low commodity prices, while employment and production capacity utilization remain steady.\\n\\nThe Russian economy has plunged into a recession amid the drop of global oil prices and Western sanctions imposed over Moscow\'s alleged intervention in the Ukraine crisis.   \\n\\nMeanwhile, the central bank kept its key interest rate unchanged at 11 percent.\\n\\nThe key interest rate has remained unchanged at 11 percent since last August, after the bank gradually lowered the rate from 17 percent, the highest level set in December 2014.\\n\\nRussia\'s currency ruble on Friday maintained the appreciation trend amid the rise of international oil prices and the central bank\'s announcement on the key interest rate.\",\"time\":1458545986},{\"contentid\":101185,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"EUROZONE INFLATION REMAINS NEGATIVE\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0321\\/101185.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0321\\/1458546046631.jpg\",\"description\":\"Latest data showed that the Eurozone annual inflation remained in the negative territory, reaching -0.2 percent in February.\\n\\nAccording to the statistics agency Eurostat, negative annual rates were observed in more than half of the member states. \\n\\nThe largest upward impacts to euro area inflation came from restaurants and cafes, rents and fruit, while fuels for transport, heating oil and gas had the biggest downward impacts.\\n\\nIn the wider 28-member EU, inflation was also -0.2 percent in February.\\n\\nThe inflation data was far from the targeted 2 percent set by the bloc\'s central bank, urging more stimulus measures. \",\"time\":1458546080},{\"contentid\":101186,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA PLAYS INCREASING ROLE IN GLOBAL INNOVATION\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en-db\\/2016\\/0321\\/101186.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0321\\/1458546114633.jpg\",\"description\":\"China has continued to perform strongly in international patent and trademark filing, amid a moderate worldwide intellectual property (IP) filing growth.\\n\\nThat is according to the latest figures released by the World Intellectual Property Organization (WIPO).\\n   \\nThe WIPO issued a report in Geneva on Wednesday, analyzing the amount and sources of global IP applications in 2015, including patents, trademarks and industrial designs.\\n\\nInternational patent applications filed under WIPO\'s Patent Cooperation Treaty (PCT) were up by 1.7 percent in 2015, the slowest growth in five years.\\n   \\nChina\'s PCT applications exceeded 29,800 last year, an increase of 16.8 percent, ranking third for the third year behind the US and Japan.\\n   \\nThe three top filing companies were China\'s Huawei Technologies, followed by U.S.-based Qualcomm and China\'s ZTE Corp. \\n\\nHuawei topped the list since 2013.\\n   \\nThe report shows that with over 2,400 applications last year, China made the most filings for international trademark applications since it became a member of the system in 1989. \\n\\nThe country was in seventh place among all filers.\\n\\nChen Hongbing, director of WIPO Office in China attributes the achievements to pursuit of an innovation-driven economy. \\n   \\nThe WIPO expects China\'s technology, products and services to benefit the world through the Belt and Road and international production capacity cooperation.\\n\\nAnd it is willing to use their innovation resources to better serve China\'s economic growth.\\n  \\nChen suggests China speed up the process of becoming a member of Hague System that governs the international registration of industrial design. \\n\",\"time\":1458546154}]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<!--{loop $data $k $r}-->\n  <li><?php $contentid=$r[\'contentid\'];?>\n\n                            <div class=\"pic pos-r\">\n                                <a href=\"{$r[url]}\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"{thumb($r[thumb],210,158,1,null,0)}\" width=\"210\" height=\"158\" alt=\"{$r[titl