,NULL,1,0,0,'{\"system_fields\":{\"contentid\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"func\":\"intval\"},\"title\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"required\":\"1\",\"min_length\":\"\",\"max_length\":\"\"},\"url\":{\"checked\":\"1\"},\"color\":{\"checked\":\"1\"},\"icon\":{\"checked\":\"1\"},\"iconsrc\":{\"checked\":\"1\"},\"subtitle\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"min_length\":\"\",\"max_length\":\"\"},\"suburl\":{\"checked\":\"1\"},\"thumb\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"width\":\"\",\"height\":\"\"},\"description\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"min_length\":\"\",\"max_length\":\"\"},\"time\":{\"checked\":\"1\",\"func\":\"section_fields_strtotime\"}},\"custom_fields\":{\"text\":[],\"name\":[]}}',1476434139,1476434139,0,0,1458225654,1,1458224400,1,'',1,0,NULL,NULL,10),(331,59,'push','英文视频首页-轮播图','[]','[{\"contentid\":214580,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"US RULES OUT CHINA CURRENCY MANIPULATOR\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1017\\/214580.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1017\\/1476686087224.jpg\",\"description\":\"U.S. Treasury Department declares that none of its major trading partner, including China, meets the standard of manipulating its currency. It still retains six economies on a monitoring list created to indicate \\\"unfair\\\" currency practices. In its Semi-Annual Report to Congress on International Economic and Exchange Rate Policies, the Treasury Department said none of its major trading partners has manipulated their currencies over the past six months to keep them undervalued.\\n   \",\"time\":1476700378},{\"contentid\":214581,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA, US FIRMS SIGN AGRICULTURAL DEALS\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1017\\/214581.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1017\\/1476686210327.jpg\",\"description\":\"More than a dozen Chinese and the U.S. enterprises on Friday signed agricultural transaction contracts worth 2.1 billion U.S. dollars. Under the deals, Chinese enterprises will import 5.1 million tons of farm products from the U.S. companies. China consumed 95 million tons of soybeans in the 2015-2016 seasonal year, and is expected to consume 98 million tons in the following seasonal year. And the demand for import will be 83 million tons, up 1.2 percent from the 2015-2016 seasonal year. \\n\",\"time\":1476699925},{\"contentid\":214582,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\" CHINA\'S LARGEST TRADE FAIR KICKS OFF \",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1017\\/214582.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1017\\/1476686273387.jpg\",\"description\":\"The China Import and Export Fair, also known as the Canton Fair, has kicked off in Guangzhou, capital of southern Guangdong Province. It\'s the country\'s largest trade fair and considered as a barometer for China\'s foreign trade. According to official statistics, in the first eight months of 2016, China\'s foreign trade slid 1.8 percent from a year earlier, with exports dropping 1 percent and imports falling 2.9 percent. But Chinese enterprises at the fair seemed to remain optimistic.\",\"time\":1476699722},{\"contentid\":214243,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"OPEC SEEKS CONSENSUS ON CUTTING OIL OUTPUT\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1013\\/214243.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1013\\/1476342610208.jpg\",\"description\":\"The Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC) says it is pursuing a global consensus on cutting oil productions. OPEC Secretary General Mohammad Barkindo Tuesday said \\\"in order to restore stability at a sustainable level, they need to work with non-OPEC members including Iran and Iraq.\\\" The chief said a global consensus becomes possible after OPEC\'s meeting last month in Algeria.\\n\",\"time\":1476351044},{\"contentid\":214245,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"HUAWEI HELPS PROMOTE TABLE BANKING IN KENYA\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1013\\/214245.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1013\\/1476342762189.jpg\",\"description\":\"Chinese ICT solutions provider, Huawei, has donated 500 smart phones worth 28,000 U.S. dollars to help promote table banking among women in Kenya. Table banking is a financial concept, whereby members gather each month and literally put their money on the table which then becomes immediately available to members as loans. It is making a difference in the lives of thousands of women and their families in rural Kenya. Huawei said the phones will be used in the automation process of the organization to support application software and enhance efficiency by eliminating paperwork.\\n\",\"time\":1476350808},{\"contentid\":214246,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"ALIBABA TO HELP SMALL BUSINESS IN THAILAND \",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1013\\/214246.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1013\\/1476342831585.jpg\",\"description\":\"Chairman of China\'s e-commerce giant Alibaba Jack Ma says his company is going to work with the Thai government to help small business in the country and to boost e-payment. For e-payment, Ma said Alibaba wants to make every shop connected with tourists to use mobile payment, making it more convenient for Chinese tourists visiting the kingdom. Besides, Ma said agricultural products of Thailand have a great potential and he hoped the online trade platform will help the farmers to sell more.\",\"time\":1476350464},{\"contentid\":213259,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"OFFICIAL PRAISES CHINESE-BUILT ELECTRIC RAILWAY \",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1009\\/213259.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1009\\/1475995748900.jpg\",\"description\":\"Ethiopia and Djibouti launched Africa\'s first modern electrified railway connecting their respective capitals on Wednesday. Officials believe the railway will have significant contribution to the countries\' economic development and technology transfer. The 752.7km electrified railway connecting the Ethiopian capital Addis Ababa and the port of Djibouti was inaugurated Wednesday in Addis Ababa. The railway also marked the first time that the complete spectrum of an overseas railway industry chain is fully backed by Chinese standards.\",\"time\":1476003740},{\"contentid\":213261,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA\'S GOLDEN WEEK SPENDING HITS RECORD HIGH\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/1009\\/213261.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/1009\\/1475995855555.jpg\",\"description\":\"Chinese has spent a record high sum of money on shopping and food during the past week-long National Day holiday, known as \\\"Golden Week\\\". According to the Ministry of Commerce, enterprises in the retail and catering sectors raked in about 1.2 trillion yuan, or 180 billion U.S. dollars from Oct. 1 to Oct. 7, up 10.7 percent. This is the second consecutive year for the \\\"Golden Week\\\" to see over one trillion yuan spending in retail and catering consumption since 1999.\",\"time\":1476003351},{\"contentid\":211918,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"ADB: ASIA GROWTH HOLDS STABLE\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/211918.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0928\\/1475029700488.jpg\",\"description\":\"The Asian Development Bank says that growth across the region is stable despite global headwinds, with resilience in China and India. According to the bank\'s latest report on Tuesday, GDP for developing Asia is predicted to grow 5.7 percent this year and the next, down slightly from 5.9 percent in 2015. ADB says the strong growth in China and India is helping the region maintain its growth momentum. The ADB also warned policymakers against any move towards protectionism.\\n\",\"time\":1475235534},{\"contentid\":212289,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"ECB EUROZONE ECONOMY SHOWS RESILIENCE\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/212289.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0929\\/1475133804629.jpg\",\"description\":\"European Central Bank President Mario Draghi says the euro area economy has showed resilience to global and political uncertainty, notably following the British referendum outcome. Draghi said the initial impact of the outcome of the UK referendum has been contained and the strong financial market reactions, such as equity price falls, have largely reversed. Meanwhile, he warned the effects on the economic outlook depend on the timing, development, and final outcome of the upcoming negotiations.\",\"time\":1475235273},{\"contentid\":212291,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"WTO CUTS TRADE GROWTH FORECAST\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/212291.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0929\\/1475133915860.jpg\",\"description\":\"The World Trade Organization has cut its forecast for global trade growth this year by more than a third. According to the latest WTO estimates published on Tuesday, world trade will grow more slowly than expected in 2016, expanding by just 1.7 percent, well below the April forecast of 2.8 percent. With expected global GDP growth of 2.2 percent in 2016, this year would mark the slowest pace of trade and output growth since the financial crisis of 2009.\\n\",\"time\":1475234142},{\"contentid\":212292,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"ADB UPGRADES CHINA\'S GROWTH FORECAST\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/212292.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"\",\"description\":\"The Asian Development Bank has slightly upgraded its forecast for China\'s annual economic growth, citing stronger-than-expected performance in the first half of this year and possible stimulus measures. The bank forecast China\'s economy will grow 6.6 percent this year, up from its March projection of 6.5 percent, with 2017 growth estimated at 6.4 percent rather than the previous estimate of 6.3 percent.\",\"time\":1475233830},{\"contentid\":211924,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"CHINA\'S SOE STRUCTURAL ADJUSTMENT FUND\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/211924.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0928\\/1475029849677.jpg\",\"description\":\"China on Monday established a national fund for structural adjustment of state-owned enterprises or SOEs. The fund has an estimated capital of around 50 billion U.S. dollars and will mainly invest in programs including scientific innovation, international operations and asset restructuring. The official said the fund will improve resource allocation and raise the efficiency of SOEs.  \",\"time\":1475233638},{\"contentid\":211920,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"BELT AND ROAD INITIATIVE MAKES PROGRESS\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/211920.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0928\\/1475029788679.jpg\",\"description\":\"According to a report published on Monday, China\'s Belt and Road Initiative has made significant progress since it was proposed three years ago. Deputy head of the Chinese Ministry of Commerce Fang Aiqin said trade between China and the Belt and Road countries exceeded 600 billion U.S. dollars during the first eight months of 2016. More than 30 countries along the new Silk Road have cooperation agreements with Beijing. China is also working with more than 20 nations on industrial capacity projects.\",\"time\":1475233536},{\"contentid\":212705,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"OPEC MEMBERS AGREE TO FREEZE OUTPUT\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/212705.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0930\\/1475218487732.jpg\",\"description\":\"The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries, or OPEC, on Wednesday  reached an agreement to freeze oil output. President of OPEC Mohammed Bin Saleh Al-Sada told a press conference after a six-hour meeting that the cartel\'s members reached the agreement to cap its oil output from 33.24 million barrels a day to 32.5 or 33 million barrels a day.\\n\",\"time\":1475233359},{\"contentid\":212707,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"ICBC DESIGNATED AS RMB CLEARING BANK IN   RUSSIA\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0930\\/212707.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0930\\/1475218599301.jpg\",\"description\":\"The People\'s Bank of China, or China\'s central bank, has authorized the Industrial and Commercial Bank of China, or ICBC, Moscow office to offer RMB clearing services in Russia. ICBC Moscow President says the move is a big step in its drive to boost international use of the Chinese currency. According to customs data, China-Russia merchandise trade grew 7.8 percent in the first eight months of 2016, sharply rebounding from a 27.8-percent decline for the whole of 2015.\",\"time\":1475233179},{\"contentid\":211782,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"BRICS KICKS OFF KEY MEETINGS\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0927\\/211782.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0927\\/1474964299648.jpg\",\"description\":\"India is set to host the 8th BRICS summit next month. Ahead of the summit, a number of meetings are held at various levels among BRICS countries. After the leaders of five BRICS countries met in Hangzhou in the G20 Leaders\' Summit earlier this month, a series of multi-lateral meetings kicked off in India. As a part of high-level engagement, security officials of the five members discussed anti-terrorism and security cooperation.\",\"time\":1474969050},{\"contentid\":211785,\"icon\":\"\",\"iconsrc\":\"\",\"title\":\"BANKER ON 1ST RMB CLEARING BANK IN US\",\"color\":\"\",\"url\":\"http:\\/\\/db.silkroad.news.cn\\/en\\/2016\\/0927\\/211785.shtml\",\"subtitle\":\"\",\"suburl\":\"\",\"thumb\":\"http:\\/\\/upload.db.silkroad.news.cn\\/2016\\/0927\\/1474964385181.jpg\",\"description\":\"China\'s central bank has authorized Bank of China\'s New York branch to provide Renminbi clearing services in the United States. It is the first time for China to set up a RMB clearing bank in the US. In an interview with CNC, President of Bank of China U.S. says the move marks a milestone for the Chinese currency on the way to become a global currency. The decision was made according to the central bank\'s memorandum of cooperation signed with the U.S. Federal Reserve Board.\",\"time\":1474968920}]',NULL,NULL,NULL,'<!--{loop $data $k $r}-->\n <li>\n <a href=\"javascript:;\" hidefocus=\"true\"><img src=\"{thumb($r[thumb],105,80,1,null,0)}\" width=\"105\" height=\"80\" alt=\"{$r[title]}\"/></a>\n\n <p>\n     <label class=\"tit-h4\"><a href=\"{$r[url]}\" target=\"_blank\">{$r[title]}</a></label>\n     <em>{date(\'Y-m-d H:i\')}</em>\n     <span>{$r